Weeping Rock, Zion National Park.

A large bowl-shaped alcove where natural spring water has been slowly descending within the sandstone formations for nearly 1,000 years. Because the Navajo Sandstone layer is porous, the alcove has continuous water seeping from its walls giving the impression that it is weeping.

Maybe this will resonate with you, or maybe it won't. I am a retired influencer (note that I am using the word "influencer" and not "creator" because I am still a creator, I just don't try to influence anymore). A lot has changed in the last few years and if you are still following me, thank you. When I started a blog nearly 15 years ago, fashion was my sole interest. When Instagram started, I was posting OOTD every single day, sometimes even three times a day. Seems a little excessive now that I think about it. At one point in my life, people even recognized me on the streets. Honestly, that feels like another lifetime ago. Today, I am sick and tired of having to pick a niche, having people/brands/society constantly telling me to pick that ONE thing and focus on that. Truth is, I like to think that I’m a well rounded person who enjoys many things. And if staying true to myself and sharing my many interests is going to cost me my engagement and likes, well then so be it.

I just finished the last DIY project in the kitchen and it finally feels like me! First, I changed the black backsplash to white subway tiles. Next, I updated the black countertop to a cement looking finish. Lastly, I decided to cover up the outdated marble floor with black and white tiles and I couldn’t be happier! And guess what? All of these are easy peel-and-stick and rental friendly. Let me know what you think of the before and after!

#homeDIY #DIYproject #homeprojects #kitchenmakeover #kitchentiles #checkeredtiles #checkeredkitchen

Today, I embark on a WEEK LONG SOLO CAMPING ROAD TRIP! I feel anxious, a bit (very) nervous, but also super excited. It's a similar feeling I had when I traveled to Europe for two weeks by myself years ago. But instead of a hotel room, I'll be in a tent; and instead of people, I'll be amongst bears. I've been dreaming of this Eastern Sierra trip for so long, it's going to be so exhilarating. Wish me luck!
